```css
* {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-style: italic;
  opacity: 0.3;
}
```

**Explanation:**
- `*` - Universal selector targets all elements
- `font-size: 20px;` - Sets font size to 20px
- `font-style: italic;` - Italicizes all text
- `opacity: 0.3;` - Applies 70% transparency (0.3 = 30% opaque, meaning 70% transparent)

**Note:** Using `opacity` affects the entire element including all children. If you want to apply transparency only to the background, use `rgba()` color values instead:

```css
* {
  font-size: 20px;
  font-style: italic;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
}
```

