# JavaScript Program to Remove Duplicates from Array

Here are several methods to remove duplicated elements:

## Method 1: Using `Set` (Simplest & Most Efficient)
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [...new Set(arr)];
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 2: Using `filter()` and `indexOf()`
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = arr.filter((item, index) => arr.indexOf(item) === index);
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 3: Using `reduce()`
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = arr.reduce((unique, item) => {
  return unique.includes(item) ? unique : [...unique, item];
}, []);
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 4: Using `forEach()` with an object
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const uniqueArr = [];
const seen = {};

arr.forEach(item => {
  if (!seen[item]) {
    uniqueArr.push(item);
    seen[item] = true;
  }
});
console.log(uniqueArr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 5: Reusable Function
```javascript
function removeDuplicates(arr) {
  return [...new Set(arr)];
}

const arr = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
console.log(removeDuplicates(arr)); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

## Method 6: For Complex Objects (using `Map`)
```javascript
const arr = [
  {id: 1, name: 'John'},
  {id: 2, name: 'Jane'},
  {id: 1, name: 'John'}
];

const uniqueArr = Array.from(
  new Map(arr.map(item => [item.id, item])).values()
);
console.log(uniqueArr);
// [{id: 1, name: 'John'}, {id: 2, name: 'Jane'}]
```

## Performance Comparison

| Method | Time | Space | Best For |
|--------|------|-------|----------|
| **Set** | O(n) | O(n) | ✅ **Best overall** |
| filter() | O(n²) | O(n) | Small arrays |
| reduce() | O(n²) | O(n) | Functional style |
| forEach() | O(n) | O(n) | Custom logic |

## Recommendation
**Use Method 1 (Set)** for most cases - it's the fastest, most concise, and most readable! ⭐

